<div id="review_208066311" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/208066311" />
    <a title="Daniel McHugh" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6293108-daniel-mchugh"><img alt="Daniel McHugh" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442488131p2/6293108.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/208066311?book_show_action=true">Sep 13, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Daniel McHugh" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Daniel McHugh" href="/user/show/6293108-daniel-mchugh">Daniel McHugh</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span> (Review from the author)


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer208066311" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11307248681750510923">I am the author of this book, therefore, I think it is a first rate, enjoyable read :) I am heavily influenced by Tolkien, Eddings, Brooks, MacDonald, Lewis, Asimov, Herbert, Card and Dahl. I believe I have a unique take on the epic quest and as the story progresses it takes the genre to places many others do not. Additionally, I have a knack for tying together a far reaching and ambitious storyline and making it cohesive and coherent. The Seraphinium not only follows the journey of one young ma</span>
  <span id="freeText11307248681750510923" style="display:none">I am the author of this book, therefore, I think it is a first rate, enjoyable read :) I am heavily influenced by Tolkien, Eddings, Brooks, MacDonald, Lewis, Asimov, Herbert, Card and Dahl. I believe I have a unique take on the epic quest and as the story progresses it takes the genre to places many others do not. Additionally, I have a knack for tying together a far reaching and ambitious storyline and making it cohesive and coherent. The Seraphinium not only follows the journey of one young man, but also the journey of nations and races. Please join me in the Nearing World. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11307248681750510923" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


